# Component Conventions

## Folder Mapping

| Folder | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `components/ui/` | Atoms / primitives — `Button`, `Avatar`, `Text`, `Icon`, `Tab`, `Skeleton`… |
| `components/shared/` | Cross-feature composites |
| `components/skeleton/` | Loading skeletons |
| `components/<feature>/` | Feature-scoped widgets — `chat/`, `post/`, `profile/`, `notification/`, `friend/` |
| `components/containers/` | Layout / screen-level wrappers |

When you add a primitive to `components/ui/`, also export it from `components/ui/index.ts`.

## Component Shape

```tsx
import { View, type ViewProps } from 'react-native';
import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge';
import { Text } from '@/components/ui';

interface CardProps extends ViewProps {
  title: string;
  className?: string;
}

export function Card({ title, className, children, ...rest }: CardProps) {
  return (
    <View
      className={twMerge(
        'rounded-lg p-4 bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark',
        className
      )}
      {...rest}
    >
      <Text variant="semibold">{title}</Text>
      {children}
    </View>
  );
}
```

Rules:
- **Named exports** only (re-exported in `components/ui/index.ts`)
- Props extend the underlying RN component props (`ViewProps`, `TouchableOpacityProps`, …)
- Always accept `className` and merge with `twMerge`
- Variant maps as `Record<Variant, string>` (see `Button.tsx`)
- Use `<Text>` from `@/components/ui` — never raw RN `<Text>`
- Use `<Icon>` from `@/components/ui` for icons (it abstracts the icon set)

## Loading & Empty States

DO NOT invent new skeletons / empty placeholders — reuse what exists:

- **Loading**: pick the matching skeleton from `@/components/skeleton/` (`HomeSkeleton`, `PostCardSkeleton`, `ProfileSkeleton`, `NotificationSkeleton`, `FriendCardSkeleton`). For ad-hoc placeholders use the primitives `Skeleton`, `SkeletonCircle`, `SkeletonText` from `@/components/ui`.
- **Empty / error list**: use `EmptyState` from `@/components/shared/ui/EmptyState` — API: `{ title: string; action?: { label, onPress } }`. Pass an `action` for retry-style affordances.
- **No `ErrorState` component exists** — for blocking errors prefer `Alert.alert`, for inline errors render `<EmptyState title="Không tải được dữ liệu" action={{ label: 'Thử lại', onPress: refetch }} />`.

```tsx
if (loading) return <PostCardSkeleton />;
if (!posts.length) {
  return (
    <EmptyState
      title="Chưa có bài viết nào"
      action={{ label: 'Làm mới', onPress: refetch }}
    />
  );
}
```

## Lists

Prefer `FlatList` / `FlashList` over `ScrollView` + `.map()` for any dynamic list.

```tsx
<FlatList
  data={posts}
  keyExtractor={(p) => p.id}
  renderItem={({ item }) => <PostCard post={item} />}
  ItemSeparatorComponent={() => <View className="h-md" />}
/>
```

## Performance

- Memoize expensive children with `React.memo` when parent re-renders frequently
- Stable callbacks via `useCallback` only when needed (avoid premature optimization)
- Heavy work off the JS thread: prefer `react-native-reanimated` worklets for animations

## Accessibility

- Touchables must have `accessibilityRole` and a meaningful `accessibilityLabel` when content is icon-only
- Hit slop ≥ 44×44 for icon buttons (`hitSlop={{ top: 8, bottom: 8, left: 8, right: 8 }}`)

## Don'ts

- ❌ Default-exported components
- ❌ Inline `StyleSheet` for new components
- ❌ Hardcoded colors — use Tailwind tokens
- ❌ `console.log` in committed code (use only for debugging, remove before commit)
